<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-02-11T14:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-02-11T14:36:00-05:00" n="794" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d794">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6091.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-11T13:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 11, 1913—1 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The fighting seems to be conducted in violation of the rules of civilized
                            warfare, as no notice has been given to noncombatants in fighting zone.
                            The direction of firing is indiscreet. The Consulate General has been
                            rendered uninhabitable and the Consul General and his staff have
                            repaired to this Embassy.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>